      "title": "What are Syllables?",
      "subtopics": [
        {
          "title": "Understanding Syllables",
          "sections": [
            {
              "text": "When we speak words, we do not say them all at once. We say them in small parts or 'beats'. Each part has one vowel sound. These small parts are called syllables. Think of it like clapping your hands for each part of a word.",
              "examples": [
                {
                  "label": "Cat",
                  "value": "cat (1 syllable)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Dog",
                  "value": "dog (1 syllable)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Run",
                  "value": "run (1 syllable)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Water",
                  "value": "wa-ter (2 syllables)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Happy",
                  "value": "hap-py (2 syllables)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Farmer",
                  "value": "far-mer (2 syllables)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Elephant",
                  "value": "el-e-phant (3 syllables)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Banana",
                  "value": "ba-na-na (3 syllables)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Hospital",
                  "value": "hos-pi-tal (3 syllables)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Information",
                  "value": "in-for-ma-tion (4 syllables)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Education",
                  "value": "ed-u-ca-tion (4 syllables)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Celebration",
                  "value": "cel-e-bra-tion (4 syllables)"
                }
              ],
              "usage_examples": [
