      "title": "Syllable Types",
      "subtopics": [
        {
          "title": "Open Syllables",
          "sections": [
            {
              "text": "An open syllable ends with a vowel sound. The vowel sound is usually long, meaning it says its name (like 'A' in 'name', 'E' in 'me', 'I' in 'hi', 'O' in 'go', 'U' in 'music').",
              "examples": [
                {
                  "label": "Go",
                  "value": "go (ends with 'o', long 'o' sound)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Me",
                  "value": "me (ends with 'e', long 'e' sound)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Hi",
                  "value": "hi (ends with 'i', long 'i' sound)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "No",
                  "value": "no (ends with 'o', long 'o' sound)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "She",
                  "value": "she (ends with 'e', long 'e' sound)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "We",
                  "value": "we (ends with 'e', long 'e' sound)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "My",
                  "value": "my (ends with 'y', long 'i' sound)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "So",
                  "value": "so (ends with 'o', long 'o' sound)"
                }
              ],
              "usage_examples": [
                "Let's 'go' to the farm.",
                "Look at 'me'!",
                "Say 'hi' to your friends.",
                "There is 'no' problem.",
                "'She' is my sister.",
                "'We' are friends.",
                "'My' book is new.",
                "'So' you understand now."
              ],
              "media": {
                "image": "images/basic/module-1/lesson-3/Open_Syllables.png"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Closed Syllables",
          "sections": [
            {
              "text": "A closed syllable ends with a consonant (any letter that is not A, E, I, O, U). The vowel sound in a closed syllable is usually short (like 'a' in 'cat', 'e' in 'bed', 'i' in 'sit', 'o' in 'hot', 'u' in 'cup').",
              "examples": [
                {
                  "label": "Cat",
                  "value": "cat (ends with 't', short 'a' sound)"
                },
                {
                  "label": "Bed",
                  "value": "bed (ends with 'd', short 'e' sound)"
